---
layout: base.njk
pageDescription: Melbourne-based software engineer available for hire, with a focus on React, React Native, TypeScript, Node.js and AWS.
---
<main>
  <div class="hero-grid" id="top">
    <section class="hero-copy">
      <p class="eyebrow">Melbourne software engineer</p>
      <h1>Available for hire.</h1>
      <p class="lead">{{ site.intro }}</p>
      <p class="availability">{{ site.availability }}</p>

      <h2>With a soft spot for thoughtful products and strong engineering teams.</h2>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="button button-primary" href="mailto:{{ site.email }}">Start a conversation</a>
        <a class="button button-secondary" href="{{ site.cvHref }}">Download CV</a>
      </div>

      <ul class="quick-notes" aria-label="Hiring notes">
        {% for note in site.hiringNotes %}
          <li>{{ note }}</li>
        {% endfor %}
      </ul>
    </section>

    <aside class="hero-card">
      <p class="card-kicker">Working style</p>
      <p class="card-copy">{{ site.summary }}</p>

      <div class="stat-grid">
        {% for stat in site.stats %}
          <article class="stat">
            <strong>{{ stat.value }}</strong>
            <span>{{ stat.label }}</span>
          </article>
        {% endfor %}
      </div>
    </aside>
  </div>

  <section class="panel panel-highlight">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">What I am looking for</p>
      <h2>The short version</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="highlight-grid">
      {% for item in site.highlights %}
        <article class="highlight-card">
          <p class="eyebrow">{{ item.eyebrow }}</p>
          <h3>{{ item.title }}</h3>
          <p>{{ item.body }}</p>
        </article>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="panel panel-focus">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">How I can help</p>
      <h2>Strongest when the work spans product, code and delivery.</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="focus-layout">
      <ul class="focus-list">
        {% for area in site.focusAreas %}
          <li>{{ area }}</li>
        {% endfor %}
      </ul>

      <div class="note-card">
        <p>
          My background includes desktop engineering, real-time simulation, distributed systems,
          front-end architecture, cloud delivery and mobile product work. The common thread is
          that I like software which has to hold up in the real world, not just in a demo.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="panel panel-commercial">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">Commercial products</p>
      <h2>Software I have worked on in the wild.</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="commercial-list">
      {% for item in site.commercialProjects %}
        <a class="commercial-link" href="/projects#project-{{ item.title | slugify }}" rel="internal">
          <strong>{{ item.title }}</strong>
          <span>{{ item.company }}</span>
        </a>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="panel panel-projects" id="projects">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">Featured work</p>
      <h2>A few things that show how I like to build.</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="project-grid">
      {% for project in site.projects %}
        <article class="project-card">
          <p class="eyebrow">{{ project.source }}</p>
          <h3>{{ project.title }}</h3>
          <p class="project-summary">{{ project.summary }}</p>
          <p>{{ project.detail }}</p>

          <div class="chip-list" aria-label="{{ project.title }} technologies">
            {% for item in project.stack %}
              <span class="chip">{{ item }}</span>
            {% endfor %}
          </div>

          <div class="project-links">
            {% for link in project.links %}
              <a href="{{ link.href }}" target="_blank" rel="nofollow external noopener noreferrer">
                {{ link.label }}
                <span class="material-symbols-outlined">{% include "open_new_tab.svg" %}</span>
              </a>
            {% endfor %}
          </div>
        </article>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>

    <p class="section-link">
      <a href="/projects/">Find out more</a>
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="panel panel-split">
    <div class="split-card">
      <p class="eyebrow">About me</p>
      <h2>A bit more context, without turning it into a TED Talk.</h2>
      <p>I like teams that value strong engineering, calm collaboration and software that feels good to use. There is a little more on how I work and what I am after on the about page.</p>
      <a class="text-link" href="/about/">Read the about page</a>
    </div>

    <div class="split-card">
      <p class="eyebrow">Experience</p>
      <h2>25+ years across desktop, web, mobile and cloud.</h2>
      <p>From Autodesk product lines and simulation tooling through to React Native, AWS and freelance delivery, I have spent a lot of time moving between hands-on engineering and technical leadership.</p>
      <a class="text-link" href="/projects/#commercial-products">Browse projects</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</main>
